---
id: runner.task.resilient
title: Task Resilient
surface: builder
platform: universal
when:
  - resilient task
  - retry plus timeout
  - health-gated task
---

Use when you need a production-shaped task with validation, resilience middleware, metadata, and cooperative cancellation.

```ts
import { Match, errors, middleware, resources, r, tags } from "@bluelibs/runner";

// Assume `paymentGateway` is a resource defined elsewhere and registered in the app.
export const chargePayment = r
  .task("chargePayment")
  .inputSchema({
    orderId: Match.NonEmptyString,
    amountCents: Match.Integer,
    currency: Match.OneOf("USD", "EUR", "GBP"),
  })
  .resultSchema({
    chargeId: Match.NonEmptyString,
    status: Match.OneOf("accepted"),
  })
  .dependencies({
    paymentGateway,
    logger: resources.logger,
  })
  .tags([tags.failWhenUnhealthy.with([paymentGateway])])
  .middleware([
    middleware.task.retry.with({
      retries: 3,
      delayStrategy: (attempt) => 250 * 2 ** attempt,
      stopRetryIf: (error) => errors.genericError.is(error),
    }),
    middleware.task.timeout.with({ ttl: 10_000 }),
  ])
  .meta({
    title: "Charge Payment",
    description:
      "Charges a payment with validation, health gating, retry, and per-attempt timeout protection.",
  })
  .throws([errors.genericError])
  .run(async (input, { paymentGateway, logger }, context) => {
    await logger.info(
      `Charging order ${input.orderId} for ${input.amountCents} ${input.currency}`,
    );

    const result = await paymentGateway.charge({
      orderId: input.orderId,
      amountCents: input.amountCents,
      currency: input.currency,
      signal: context.signal,
    });

    if (result.kind === "declined") {
      throw errors.genericError.new({
        message: `Payment declined for order ${input.orderId}`,
      });
    }

    return {
      chargeId: result.chargeId,
      status: "accepted" as const,
    };
  })
  .build();
```

Notes:
- Keep `retry` outermost and `timeout` inside when you want per-attempt budgets.
- Forward `context.signal` to downstream work.
- Do not cram cache, auth, rate-limit, and circuit-breaker into the same starter snippet.
